Description
AddAppointmentController
The AddAppointmentController class is responsible for the implementation of the Add Appointment screen and its associated functionality.
AddCustomerController
Controller for the Add Customer scene.
Appointment
This class represents an appointment, containing information such as the appointment's id, title, description, location, type, start and end time, creation date and user, last update and user, customer id, user id, and contact id.
AppointmentAccess
This abstract class provides access to the appointments table in the database.
AppointmentsController
The AppointmentsController class is the controller for the appointments scene.
Contact
The Contact class represents a contact in the database containing information such as contactId, contactName, and email.
ContactAccess
Abstract class to provide access to contact information stored in a database.
Country
The Country class represents a country in the database containing information such as countryId, country, createDate, createdBy, lastUpdate, and lastUpdatedBy.
CountryAccess
The CountryAccess class provides methods for interacting with the countries table in the database.
Customer
The Customer class represents a customer in the database containing information such as customerId, customerName, address, postalCode, phone, createDate, createdBy, lastUpdate, lastUpdatedBy, and divisionId.
CustomerAccess
Abstract class containing methods for accessing and modifying customer data in the database.
CustomerReport
Class representing a customer report containing the customer's ID and the country they are located in.
CustomersController
The controller class for the Customers screen.
CustomerWithDivision
A class that represents a customer with their associated division and country.
DialogBox
The DialogBox class is a utility class that contains static methods for displaying alert and confirmation dialogs to the user.
FirstLevelDivision
The FirstLevelDivision class represents a first level division in the database, containing information such as divisionId, division, createDate, createdBy, lastUpdate, lastUpdatedBy, and countryId.
FirstLevelDivisionAccess
A class for accessing the `first_level_divisions` table in the database.
JDBC
The JDBC class is responsible for managing the connection to the MySQL database.
LoadSceneHelper
The LoadSceneHelper class provides a helper method for loading a new scene in the application.
LogActivity
This class represents the log activity of successful and failed logins in the system.
LoginAccess
This class provides methods for accessing the users table in the database.

A controller class for the login scene in the DBClientApp application.
Main
The main class that launches the application and manages the database connection.
MainMenuController
The MainMenuController class is the controller for the main menu screen.
MonthReport
The MonthReport class represents a report containing information about the number of appointments for a given month, including the month name and the total number of appointments.
ReportAccess
Provides methods for generating reports from the database.
ReportsController
Controller class for the reports page of the application.
Resources
This abstract class extends the ListResourceBundle class and is used to store string values for use in the application.
Resources_en
This class is a concrete subclass of the abstract Resources class.
Resources_fr
A class representing a resource bundle for French language.
TypeReport
The TypeReport class represents a type report in the database containing information such as the total number of appointments of a certain type and the type itself.
UpdateAppointmentController
The UpdateAppointmentController class is the controller class for the Update Appointment window.
UpdateCustomerController
The UpdateCustomerController class is responsible for handling the logic for updating customer information in the database.
User
The User class represents a user in the database containing information such as userId, userName, password, createDate, createdBy, lastUpdate, and lastUpdatedBy.
UserAccess
This abstract class provides access to user data in the database.
